children.subject: If you go to Prof. Sahai's website, you can see which semesters he has taught EE16B.

history.content:
If its not on https://coursecapture.berkeley.edu/el-eng-16b, there's good chance that the webcasts are unavailable.

______________________________________________________________________________________________

Pr. Sahai taught EE16B in Spring 2016. The course has changed and restructured itself a lot since then, but the recordings were only posted on the piazza page I think (linked to private videos on the EE department channel).
If its not on https://coursecapture.berkeley.edu/el-eng-16b, there's good chance that the webcasts are unavailable.

history.content:
Has Pr. Sahai ever done EE 16B? If so was it webcast?

I am right now going through his Fall 2017 16A webcasts/homework/discussions in order to prep for CS 189, and I REALLY like how he teaches the material.

I would love to be able to go through 16B material by watching his webcasts if possible, but unfortunately I don't see them here:

https://coursecapture.berkeley.edu/el-eng-16b
